    "narrative": {
      "type": "seth-narrative",
      "blocks": {
        "left_1": {
          "type": "left_paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Nancy's journey began with a spiritual encounter that changed the course of her life. She saw children across the nations, lacking food and covering. In that moment, a voice spoke: <strong>\"Start designing. Reach out to these children and let them know they are loved—that they are true royalty.\"</strong></p>"
          }
        },
        "left_2": {
          "type": "left_paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Later, her eyes were opened to a vision of a breathtaking garden. The instruction was clear: <strong>\"I will have you build the garden of the Lord all around the world.\"</strong> For Nancy, fashion became the vehicle—a platform to restore identity and elevate humanity to its original regal design.</p>"
          }
        },
        "right_1": {
          "type": "right_paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>In perfect alignment, Dionne received a vision of a girl in a garden, hearing the declaration: <em><strong>\"Her name is Eden. I will find my rest in her.\"</strong></em> Then came the vision of a boy, Seth—a name meaning <em><strong>\"The Appointed One.\"</strong></em></p>"
          }
        },
        "right_2": {
          "type": "right_paragraph",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>When these two visions converged, Seth Eden was born. It is a house built on the intersection of <strong>Restoration and Authority</strong>. Every garment is crafted to reflect the \"True Royalty\" Nancy was called to champion, and the \"Appointment\" Dionne was shown.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "left_1",
        "left_2",
        "right_1",
        "right_2"
      ],
      "settings": {
        "eyebrow_left": "The Global Mandate",
        "heading_left": "Nancy Vuu: Building the Garden.",
        "eyebrow_right": "The Appointed Names",
        "heading_right": "Dionne Husted: The Rest & The Appointment",
        "closing_quote": "\"We do not just create garments; we clothe the calling of a generation.\"",
        "foundation_eyebrow": "Restorative Commerce",
        "foundation_heading": "Elevating Humanity.",
        "foundation_body_1": "Seth Eden exists for more than just aesthetics. We are a house of Restorative Commerce. A portion of every commission directly funds initiatives that restore dignity, provide covering, and uplift communities across the nations.",
        "foundation_body_2": "Your investment in a custom garment extends far beyond your wardrobe—it becomes a seed in the garden of humanity's restoration. This is the original mandate that called Nancy Vuu into design, and it remains the heartbeat of everything we create."
      }
    },
